                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d182">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.48/3409: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to The
                        Chargé in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Matthews</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-01-22T14:00:00-04:00"
                            >January 22, 1943—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>479. Your 319, January 13, 4 p.m. This Government is prepared to agree to this
                    proposal as outlined.</p>
                <p>We would have no objection to granting the Swedes an increase in their oil quotas
                    to compensate for the initial bunkers and lubricants <pb facs="0182" n="170"
                        xml:id="pg_170"/> furnished for this vessel within a maximum of 150 tons of
                    diesel oil and 5 tons of lubricants. If other arrangements could not be made, we
                    would also be prepared to permit the export of reasonable quantities of bunkers
                    and lubricants on the relief vessels from Canada for operation of the ship in
                    Greek waters, provided satisfactory assurances were received that the supplies
                    would be strictly controlled by the Relief Commission and used only for the
                    relief ship, and that full reports would be submitted regarding their use.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Stockholm.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
